meta-docker-config
==================

This layer contains small Yocto customizations for Docker-based images.
It currently focuses on boot-time service behavior by:

- removing `systemd-networkd-wait-online.service`
- installing a simplified `docker.service`
- enabling the Docker service automatically at image creation time


Dependencies
============

This layer declares the following formal dependency in
`conf/layer.conf`:

- `core`

In practice, the Docker recipe append in this layer is only useful when the
build also includes a layer that provides `docker-moby`, such as
`meta-virtualization`.

This layer is compatible with the `scarthgap` Yocto release series.


Contents
========

- `conf/layer.conf`
  Registers the layer, its file search paths, priority, and compatibility.

- `recipes-core/systemd/systemd_%.bbappend`
  Removes `systemd-networkd-wait-online.service` and its enablement symlink
  during installation so the image no longer blocks boot waiting for
  `systemd-networkd` to report the network as online.

- `recipes-docker-config/docker-moby/docker-moby_%.bbappend`
  Adds a custom `docker.service`, registers it with systemd packaging, and
  enables it by default in the generated image.

- `recipes-docker-config/docker-moby/files/docker.service`
  Overrides the Docker unit dependency ordering so Docker starts after
  `network.target` and `containerd.service` instead of waiting for
  `network-online.target`.


Behavior
========

The service customizations in this layer are intended for systems where:

- Docker should start automatically on boot
- waiting for full network-online synchronization is unnecessary or slows boot
- the board uses a simpler network bring-up sequence

The installed Docker unit uses:

- `After=network.target containerd.service`
- `Wants=containerd.service`
- `ExecStart=/usr/bin/dockerd -H fd://`
- `Restart=always`

Because `systemd-networkd-wait-online.service` is removed, services should not
assume that an interface has a lease or external connectivity at the moment
`multi-user.target` is reached. This is usually acceptable for Docker on
embedded systems, but it is worth validating if your containers depend on
network availability during early boot.


Adding The Layer
================

Add the layer to your build:

`bitbake-layers add-layer ../sources/meta-docker-config`

Then ensure your build also includes the layer that provides `docker-moby`
and that your image installs Docker.


Notes
=====

- This layer does not provide the Docker engine recipe itself; it only
  customizes recipes supplied by other layers.
- If another layer also modifies `docker.service` or the systemd install
  stage, review layer priority and final packaged unit contents carefully.
- If your platform requires strict boot-time network readiness, you may want
  to keep `systemd-networkd-wait-online.service` enabled instead of using this
  layer as-is.
